From: teffta@cs690-3.erie.ge.com (Andrew R. Tefft)
Subject: Re: Linux and Corporate America
Reply-To: teffta@cs690-3.erie.ge.com
Date: Tue, 31 Aug 1993 16:27:06 GMT

Look at it this way: since Linus (or anyone else) is not making money
off of Linux, what's he got to lose from someone plagarizing it?
Prestige? (ask him if he wants it.) The time he has spent on it?  Not
really lost, since presumably Linux would not die completely just from
someone plagarizing it. In order for anyone to sue for damages there
have to be some damages... and the amount of protection you afford
something like your copyright on Linux should be proportional to your
potential damages!

The only thing I can possibly imagine Linus (or any of us) really could
lose is the freedom to continue developing it, i.e. if someone managed
to legally say "This is now mine and it is no longer under the GPL, you
may not change it or have the source code or give it to anyone."


