From: hdhumphr@eos.ncsu.edu (HAL DOUGLAS HUMPHREY)
Subject: FDISK on IDE + ESDI system-ESDI not recognised
Date: Tue, 31 Aug 1993 19:02:29 GMT

I am trying to install Linux for the first time.
My system is a 386/33, 16meg ram, 100meg IDE (2 FAT partitions
plus OS/2 Boot Manager), and a 320 meg ESDI.

The IDE is the main controller and is defined in BIOS.
The ESDI is the secondary controller and is accessed through
device drivers in DOS and OS/2 with no problem.

When I try to FDISK from Linux, only the IDE is recognized.
Any attempt to access /dev/hdb fails.
Is there any way to get Linux to work with the IDE?
Even just being able to install and use it without access to the 
IDE drive would be OK.

Thanks
Hal

